  author={Tedoldi, Riccardo and De Rito, Carlo and Malatesta, Marco and Iotti, Eleonora and Dal Palù, Alessandro and Percudani, Riccardo},
  abstract={Neofunctionalization is a process by which a gene acquires a new function after a duplication event. The detection of neofunctionalization events is a challenging task, as it requires the comparison of the function of the ancestral gene with the function of the descendant genes. In this work, we propose a machine learning approach to detect neofunctionalization events. We use Transformer-based models to encode the protein sequences using different sources of information. We use a manually curated dataset, reaching an accuracy of 90\% in recognizing neofunctionalization events over the testset.},
